The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, September 01, 2003  Calcutta Column
 
	Traffic rules allow autorickshaws to carry a maximum of  four passengers. But in crowded areas like NSC Bose Road  and Behala, autos carrying five passengers go scot-free.  This puts passengers at a great risk. 
	 Jagdish Kumar, Chittaranjan Avenue.  
	It has become an annoying trend among companies selling  consumer durable products to advertise their goods by pasting  slogans on the walls of residential complexes. This accompanies  graffiti put up by political parties. Since the Calcutta  Municipal Corporation is taking up measures to beautify  the city, it should look into this as well.  
	Ranu Mukherjee, Bagbazar. 

